The paper proposes a new evolutionary algorithm for solving optimization problems, which falls under the category of machine learning and optimization. Specifically, the algorithm uses pairwise linkage detection and dependency structure matrix (DSM) to exploit problem substructures, which suggests a focus on neural networks and artificial intelligence (cs.NE, cs.AI). The paper also introduces new concepts such as incremental linkage set and restricted back mixing, which are related to optimization techniques and algorithms (cs.DS). The experimental results and comparison with other algorithms suggest a focus on performance evaluation and analysis (cs.LG), and the paper also includes implementation details and considerations, which suggest a focus on software engineering (cs.SE).
